      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Melee Tactics Toolbox pg. 19</em></p><h3 class=\"framing\"><img src=\"https://www.aonprd.com/images/PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif\" title=\"PFS Legal\" style=\"margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;\">Statistics</h3><p><strong>Cost</strong> 5 gp <strong>Weight</strong> 4 lbs.</p><p><strong>Damage</strong> 1d4 (small), 1d6 (medium); <strong>Critical</strong> x3; <strong>Range</strong> -; <strong>Type</strong> P; <strong>Special</strong> grapple</p><p><strong>Category</strong> Two-Handed; <strong>Proficiency</strong> Simple</p><p><strong>Weapon Groups</strong> Axes</p><h3 class=\"framing\">Description</h3><p>Adapted from a garden rake, the kumade consists of a wood or bamboo pole topped with a metal claw. The rake head doubles as a grappling hook. When a kumade is secured to a surface, such as a rafter or window sill, its handle can be climbed as a 5-foot length of rope.</p>"
